1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Radar doesn't need light — it listens for radio echoes bouncing off objects.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:06,800
How does it work?

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:10,800
Radar sends out pulses of radio waves, like invisible messengers.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:15,200
When these waves hit an object, they bounce back, creating echoes.

5
00:00:15,200 --> 00:00:20,400
By measuring the time it takes for echoes to return, radar calculates distance.

6
00:00:20,400 --> 00:00:26,000
This means radar can see through fog, revealing what’s ahead, even in zero visibility.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,800
Want to dive deeper into radar tech?

8
